The paper discusses the challenges associated with big data volume, velocity, and variety, and proposes a technique called Dimensional Data Analysis (DDA) to quickly understand the overall structure of a big dataset and determine anomalies. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the database (cs.DB), data structures (cs.DS), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), machine learning (cs.LG), or information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-categories.
